net.grinder.statistics
Class StatisticsIndexMap

java.lang.Object
  net.grinder.statistics.StatisticsIndexMap
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public final class StatisticsIndexMap
extends Object
implements Serializable

A register of statistic index objects.

Each statistic has a unique index object and a name. The index objects are used with Statisticsand the names can be used in expressions (see ExpressionView). Statistics can either be long integer values (see getLongIndex(java.lang.String)) or double floating-point values (getDoubleIndex(java.lang.String)).

The standard long statistics used by The Grinder are:

  • errors
  • untimedTests
  • period

Additionally, there are five long statistics that scripts and custom plug-ins can use for their own purposes, userLong0, userLong1, ... userLong4.

The standard double statistics used by The Grinder are:

  • peakTPS

Additionally, there are five double statistics for use by scripts and custom plugins, userDouble0,userDouble1, ... userDouble4.

There is a special type of index object for sample statistics, see StatisticsIndexMap.LongSampleIndex,getLongSampleIndex(java.lang.String), StatisticsIndexMap.DoubleSampleIndex,getDoubleSampleIndex(java.lang.String). Sample statistics are the result of a series of sample values. The values can be either longs or doubles. Sample statistics have three attribute values that can be read: the count (number of samples), sum (total of all sample values), and sample variance. These attributes can be queried using the appropriate expression function (e.g. count()), see ExpressionView.

The standard long sample statistics used by The Grinder are:

  • timedTests

There are no standard double sample statistics.

There is currently no provision for user specified sample statistics.

Author:
Philip Aston
